@dior is expanding its lifestyle offering with Haute Wellness, a new collection designed by Cordelia de Castellane that focuses on movement, mindfulness, and better sleep. The range combines a selection of fitness and wellness essentials, all finished with subtle nods to the House, including the signature cannage motif embroidered in gold thread on a palette of blue and ivory.⁠
⁠
The collection includes workout accessories such as resistance bands, weights, yoga and Pilates mats, and water bottles, alongside sleep-focused pieces like a silk pillowcase and eye mask. Rounding out the lineup is the 5 Minutes Journal, designed to encourage a few moments of daily reflection through prompts and quotes.⁠

@underarmour is making its boldest push into fashion yet as it celebrates 30 years in business, kicking off a new wave of collaborations with Paris-based label @marineserre_official. Premiered exclusively by Highsnobiety, the partnership draws from Under Armour's 2000s archives, finding common ground between the brand's performance-focused HeatGear baselayers and Marine Serre's signature "Second Skin" design language. The result is a collection of compression layers and technical apparel featuring Serre's iconic moon motif integrated throughout, alongside the revival of a late-2000s running shoe updated with subtle monochrome gradients.⁠
⁠
The collaboration signals a new direction for Under Armour, following recent projects with 424 and growing speculation around a wider partnership with Playboi Carti's Opium collective. Unlike its headline-making Balenciaga collaboration in 2024, Marine Serre represents a younger, more niche fashion audience, underscoring Under Armour's increasing alignment with contemporary luxury and streetwear culture. The collection launches June 5 via Marine Serre's website.⁠

@a.presse_ latest collection, Fall/Winter 2026 (or “2026 STYLE2”), takes the brand’s familiar approach of recreating rugged vintage Americana through artful and often unexpected materials, but with a noticeably grungier edge. Worn by the shaggy-haired model synonymous with past campaigns, the collection feels darker, shabbier, and more pronounced in its louche scruffiness, from untidy layering and baggy silhouettes to silver wallet chains and dramatic lighting.⁠
⁠
If one look captures the season, it’s a relaxed Type III trucker jacket inspired by Levi’s, cut from a washed silk-cotton blend and styled with a half-unbuttoned check shirt and another tied at the waist. The collection continues A.PRESSE’s signature tension between worn-out Americana and luxurious craftsmanship, pairing purposefully aged sweaters and washed work shirts with delicate fabrics and meticulous construction. For Fall/Winter 2026, that formula remains intact, only now with the grit dialed up even further.⁠

@marineserre_official and @underarmour are rewriting the sportswear playbook. The duo’s debut collaboration reworks archival performance gear through Serre’s signature high-fashion lens. Expect second-skin silhouettes, technical fabrics and a custom crescent moon-meets-heartbeat logo print. Plus, the UA Proto Speed II sneaker is officially back for the first time since the late 2000s.
The collection drops June 5. Will you be wearing this to the gym?
Images: Under Armor, Marine Serre

@Charli_XCX annuncia il nuovo album — e il titolo dice già tutto. Music, Fashion, Film arriva il 24 luglio, con i singoli già usciti SS26 e Rock Music. La copertina, fotografata da Aidan Zamiri, mette insieme John Cale, @TheMarcJacobs e Martin Scorsese. Tre universi, una sola immagine. Ci sembra esattamente il tipo di album che non si può ignorare.
